<Review ID>7894040
<Product Name>Creative Zen 16 GB (Black)
<Title>The Best Media Player I Have Seen
<Date>Mon Jan 07 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>Most of the reviews here got it right: the display quality is awesome and a 16 GB capacity goes a long way (not to mention the SD expansion capability).  Photos and Videos look great.  The software interface is beautiful and has the glass feel to it.  No need to install the included software: transfering music, photos, and videos is plug-and-play easy from Windows Media Player - just connect the device and drag-and-drop (album art is automatically transferred).  I owned a Sansa device and this one is magnitudes better in all categories.  Although I give the player 5 stars, everything around it gets about 3.  The USB cord is 3 inches long!, there is essentially no manual - you got to figure it out on your own, and any firmware upgrade may likely end in technical problems only to be resolved by obscure web-based articles that the avergage user may have trouble finding and using.  And I *really* do not like when companies bury their technical support phone number deep into an obscure help file located only on the CD.  However, if you can get through these things, the device itself is well worth the effort and you'll be very pleased.  
<Overall>5

<Review ID>6663707
<Product Name>Creative Zen 16 GB (Black)
<Title>Beware Creative Zen
<Date>Tue Jan 08 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>Do NOT buy the Create Zen 16 GB MP3 player. Although it gets glowing reviews from journalists, they neglect to tell you about the tendency of this device to become useless when the firmware upgrade dies.My Zen didn't even last 30 minutes out of the package. First you install software, then update that software, then update the firmware. All seemed to go well until the Zen tried to reset itself after the firmare update.No joy. It's dead with no OS. I had to send it back.  
<Overall>1

<Review ID>9482103
<Product Name>Creative Zen 16 GB (Black)
<Title>Powerfull MP3 player in a small package!
<Date>Tue Jan 08 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>First off let me say I bought this to replace a 30 gig Vision:M, I also bought a 80 gig Zune which I quickly returned and opted for a second 16gb Zen.  As of right now I own three 16gb Zens.    The reason I gave it a 4 instead of a 5 is there have been only a 2 or 3 incidents where i have had to hard reset, then resync because it messed up my playlists, that is the only issue i have had with the players and my guess is it will be fixed with a firmware upgrade at some point.  Anyhow, I was pretty excited to get a flash based player that was big enough to hold my music and photos, it loads album art instantly, which is something you can't really say about any of the hard drive players.  It's solid and well built, I opted for a screen protector and one of the rubber skins which i am very happy with.  Sound quality is really where the creative products shine, although the included headphones are nothing to get excited about.  Screen size and quality are very good, especially when you consider the player is the size of a credit card.  Battery lilfe is good, it's great if you lock it and shut off the screen.  I purchase the zen products because they sync easily with Windows Media Player, I actually like WMP so I rarely use the creative sync software.  It syncs quickly and uses a STANDARD USB cable, that's right no proprietary cable, which is again rare in any of the players on the market.  There's a lot of accessories available for the Zen's which I have found in the past to lacking for any non-ipod model, but I think we'll continue to more accessories for this little player.  Creative made a great decision adopting the flash based players early on and they are one of the very few with 16 gig+ players.  
<Overall>4

<Review ID>5042163
<Product Name>Creative Zen 16 GB (Black)
<Title>Awesome versatile mp3 player
<Date>Fri Jan 11 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>This replaced a Creative Micro Photo 8gb (micro hard drive) with which I was extremely pleased with for two years.  I bought the 4gb version of this player for may father's Christmas present, and I was so jealous I got myself the 16gb version.  This little device is incredibly versatile.  Plays mp3 with great sound (but buy better earphones), plays video on a great 2.5" screen, has an FM radio built in, microphone, and even has a slot for sd memory cards, something I haven't seen in a similar device.  I use Windows Media Player to manage songs (but need the supplied software to handle playlists).  I occasionally use a remote designed for earlier versions that connects via the headphones jack so I can keep it on a belt clip while exercising.  I wish the Creative software was better, but that's really not a problem.  It's a much better value than a similar iPod.  The only advantages iPods have over it is the abundance of accessories and easy integration with iTunes (can work around that).  I highly recommend this one, though there's already a 32gb version.  I expect in a couple of years to buy a replacement that's 64 gb or more and with bells and whistles I can only dream of (built in Bluetooth?) from Creative.  Remember, these are the guys who invented the iPod touch dial interface!  
<Overall>5

<Review ID>7508783
<Product Name>Creative Zen 16 GB (Black)
<Title>This is a fantastic product
<Date>Fri Jan 11 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I have had it for over a month and love it.  I did upgrade the headphones (I got the sennheiser buds which are very good) so I agree with other users who have done the same.  In my case the provided ones didn't feel comfortable in my ears.  Sound is excellent   I listen to most types of music Video is excellent   I watched all three seasons of Battlestar Galactica from Unbox Features are excellent   I have really just begun playing with these but they all work as advertised.  I highly recommend this product.  I bought my daughter an iPod Nano 8gb for Christmas and I like it, too.  But I really don't like the iTunes interface which has behaved strangely on both my computers.  In the worst case it got into an endless cycle of 'restoring' the iPod . . .  In any case the player is also nice but lacks the expandable memory and has a smaller screen.  I might recommend that you hold out for the 32GB version which should be available.  But you won't be sorry you bought any one of these.    
<Overall>5

<Review ID>4922601
<Product Name>Creative Zen 16 GB (Black)
<Title>Finally....
<Date>Sat Jan 12 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I used to have ZEN 8GB which had WSOD problem with the firmware 1.20.02 and I had to reset the player with a paper clip everytime I switched  it on, therefore I returned it to the store.(I did not purchase that one from Amazon, though)   However I did like ZEN's nice sound/video quality so I ordered 16GB to Amazon to try just one more time. I was indeed so afraid of WSOD when I  updated the firmware but it has been 3 days and has been working great without any problem.(no single freeze or WSOD happened for 3 days) Thank you so much Amazon! Amazon's shipment was also very prompt!  I love this small player and I carry it whenever/whereever I travel.  I strongly recommend this player and hope that those who is thinking  to purchase ZEN will get a good batch which is free from WSOD. If you happened to receive a bad batch and experienced WSOD, you can just return the defective one and try again.                
<Overall>5

