<Content>The player is fine, well made and functions as advertised.  I have a single complaint, one that rules it out for my use: one cannot organize music into folders and have those show up as folders that can be opened in a search mode.  The iAudio units do this perfectly but it seems not possible to overcome ID3 tags with Creative.  When scrolling, I would like to see, for example, folders labelled 'Broadway', 'Folk', 'Opera', 'Books', etc. and then open the selected folder to choose an item.  If this is possible with Creative then it takes more steps and requires more patience than I'm willing to expend especially given the ease with which this is accomplished by iAudio.  I returned the Creative Zen 16gb and will replace it with the iAudio 7 player: smaller screen but, from my perspective, much better options for organizing contents.<a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000UVBDRS/ref=cm_cr_asin_lnk/105-6954301-3468444">Creative Zen 16 GB (Black)</a>  
